  "target_response": {
    "text": "With rotating shifts, the goal shifts from a perfect night to a protected anchor. Right now you're running lean on both counts: last night's 5.8 hours is under your 7-day average of 6.2 hours, and that average itself sits well short of your 7.5-hour sleep need. Your consistency score of 48% reflects the rotation — that part isn't fully fixable, but it is compressible. Two moves that work around shifts rather than against them: pick a four-hour anchor window that stays identical across every shift pattern and treat it as non-negotiable, and make day sleep dark and quiet enough to pass for night — blackout, earplugs, phone outside the room. Judge success by the 7-day average trending toward 7 hours, not by any single day.",
